iiitb:btech_integrated_mtech a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "B.Tech. & Integrated M.Tech." ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "Applications for the Academic Year 2026–27 will be updated soon. B.Tech and Integrated M.Tech Programmes Admissions to the below programmes are through a common application process. Individual applications to the respective programmes are NOT needed. Click on the following tabs for detailed information about the admissions to the above programmes. [25 February, 2026] : Online Application Pre Registration Note: Complete Application Submission opens (after JEE Main final results) This page will be updated once the seat allocation process starts. Applicants must have completed 10+2 (or equivalent) with a first-class grade and Mathematics as one of the subjects. Students who are expected to meet this requirement by July 2026 are also eligible to apply. Additionally, a valid JEE Main score from" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/courses/btech-integrated-mtech" .

iiitb:centre_for_applied_sciences a edu:Lab ;
    rdfs:label "Centre for Applied Sciences" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "At CAS we work in physics & mathematics, making advances in both fundamental as well as applied fields across multiple disciplines, laying the necessary theoretical foundations for many a practical edifice. The Centre for Applied Sciences comprises of a group of physicists and mathematicians working in diverse fields, from nonlinear dynamics, complex systems & soft matter physics, to computational fluid dynamics & magnetohydrodynamics, to number theory & diophantine equations, to mathematical modelling & numerical simulations of thin films. The CAS is administratively under the Dept of Electronics & Communications Engineering. We support teaching efforts in mathematics and physics courses in programs across all the departments at IIITB. We have an active, ongoing research program, taking i" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/centre-for-applied-sciences" .

iiitb:centre_for_it_public_policy_citapp a edu:Lab ;
    rdfs:label "Centre for IT & Public Policy (CITAPP)" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "The Center for Information Technology and Public Policy (CITAPP) focuses on the policy challenges and the organizational demands made by technological innovation. The Center is interested in interactions between technology and society and particularly how technological advances, along with institutional changes that harness the legitimacy and the powers of bureaucracies and market, address the needs of under-served communities. It seeks to provide a means to nurture and transform public policy through the use of Information and Communication Technologies (ICTs) by engaging with academic faculty and researchers, policy planners, political leaders and community representatives, technology vendors, public officials and civil society organizations. The Center brings together best-practices dem" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/centre-for-it-public-policy-citapp" .

