    edu:description "Memorandum of Understanding Between International Institute of Information Technology Bangalore Innovation Centre and Sungkyunkwan University Startup Support Foundation Bengaluru, October 10, 2024: Innovation Centre at International Institute of Information Technology Bangalore (IIIT-B) and Sungkyunkwan University (SKKU) Startup Support Foundation signed a significant Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) on September 27, 2024, at the Natural Science Campus of SKKU in Suwon, Gyeonggi Province, South Korea. This MoU is aimed at fostering collaboration and knowledge exchange to strengthen startup support between universities in India and South Korea. The primary objectives of this partnership include: Professor Kim Kyung-hwan , Director, Sungkyunkwan University Startup Support Foundation and Dea" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/media/memorandum-of-understanding-between-international-institute-of-information-technology-bangalore-innovation-centre-and-sungkyunkwan-university-startup-support-foundation" .

iiitb:microsoft_and_iiit_bangalore_launch_a4i_the_ai_innovation_and_inclusion_initiative_to_drive_scalable_ai_for_societal_impact a edu:Lab ;
    rdfs:label "Microsoft and IIIT-Bangalore Launch \"A4I – the AI Innovation and Inclusion Initiative\" to Drive Scalable AI for Societal Impact" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "Microsoft and IIIT-Bangalore Launch \"A4I – the AI Innovation and Inclusion Initiative\" to Drive Scalable AI for Societal Impact Bengaluru, India, April 25, 2025 — Microsoft and the International Institute of Information Technology Bangalore (IIIT-B) today announced the launch of A4I – the AI Innovation and Inclusion Initiative , a collaborative effort aimed at advancing the use of artificial intelligence (AI) to create inclusive, impactful, and scalable solutions for underserved communities. AI holds immense potential to drive meaningful change, especially in areas such as healthcare, education, and accessibility. However, for these technologies to truly benefit society, they must be designed with intentionality and inclusiveness and supported through sustainable partnerships. A4I is roote" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/media/microsoft-and-iiitbangalore-launch-a4i-the-ai-innovation-and-inclusion-initiative-to-drive-scalable-ai-for-societal-impact" .

iiitb:msc_digital_society a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Sc. (Digital Society)" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "The International Institute of Information Technology Bangalore (IIIT-Bangalore) invites you to be a part of an interdisciplinary Master's Program in Digital Society. The two-year program is a blend of topics drawn from information technology and social sciences. It trains new-age professionals to design, deploy and develop digital technologies for diverse populations across domains like governance, healthcare, education, infrastructures, media to name a few. In our efforts to create an equitable and inclusive digital society, our graduates will be able to, If you believe in building a career in technology that impacts society, this program is tailor-made just for you. This two-week orientation will consist of a series of sessions, including lectures, readings, and audio-visual media to ex" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/academics/masters-programmes/msc-digital-society" .

iiitb:mtech a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Tech." ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "2-year Master of Technology programme in Computer Science & Engineering (CSE) 2-year Master of Technology programme in Electronics & Communication Engineering (ECE). 2-year Master of Technology programme in Artificial Intelligence & Data Science (AI & DS). 26/C, Opposite of Infosys Gate 10 Electronics City Phase 1, Hosur Road Bengaluru - 560100 © 2026 IIIT-Bangalore. All Rights Reserved" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/mtech" .

iiitb:mtech_ai_ds_admissions a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Tech. AI & DS Admissions" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "Applications for the Academic Year 2026–27 are now open. [March 19, 2026]: Applications for the Academic Year 2026–27 are open. Candidates can apply via the link https://admissions.iiitb.net/ The minimum qualification for admission to the M.Tech (AI & DS) programme is 65% in four-year bachelor's degree in engineering (i.e. B.E., B.Tech., or equivalent) in any one of the branches. Those having MSc(CSE/Math/Statistics/Operational Research) degree are eligible to apply to the M.Tech. (AI&DS) programme . Such students are eligible to apply with a condition that they have BSc in Computer Science or BSc in any other subject with Mathematics as one of the courses. Final-year students expecting to graduate by July 2026 may also apply. Admissions to the M.Tech (AI&DS) programme is on the basis of p" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/courses/mtech-ai-ds-admissions" .

iiitb:mtech_artificial_intelligence_and_data_science a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Tech (Artificial Intelligence and Data Science)" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "The goal of post graduate programmes at IIIT-Bangalore is to develop professionals of high quality to cater to the needs of industry and academia. Such education will be based on a broad grasp of the fundamental principles of the sciences and scientific methods, a deep understanding of a specific area of specialization, an ability to solve new problems, and a capacity to learn continually and interact with multidisciplinary groups. Above all, IIIT-Bangalore aims at developing in its students a capacity for free and objective inquiry, courage and integrity, and awareness and sensitivity to the needs and aspirations of society. The postgraduate programmes are designed with the above goals in view. They include courses of study, seminars, project work, internships and research leading to a th" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/academics/masters-programmes/mtech-artificial-intelligence-and-data-science" .

iiitb:mtech_computer_science_and_engineering a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Tech (Computer Science and Engineering)" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "The goal of post graduate programs at IIIT-B is to develop professionals of high quality to cater to the needs of industry and academia. Such education will be based on a broad grasp of the fundamental principles of the sciences and scientific methods, a deep understanding of specific area of specialization, an ability to solve new problems, and a capacity to learn continually and interact with multidisciplinary groups. Above all, IIIT-B aims at developing in its students a capacity for free and objective enquiry, courage and integrity, and awareness and sensitivity to the needs and aspirations of society. The postgraduate programs are designed with the above goals in view. They include courses of study, seminars, project work, internships, and research leading to a thesis. M.Tech in Compu" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/academics/masters-programmes/mtech-computer-science-and-engineering" .

iiitb:mtech_cse_admissions a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Tech. CSE Admissions" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "Applications for the Academic Year 2026–27 are now open. [March 19, 2026]: Applications for the Academic Year 2026–27 are open. Candidates can apply via the link https://admissions.iiitb.net/ You can download a FREE IIIT-B admission brochure . The minimum qualification for admission to the M.Tech (CSE) programme is 65% in four-year bachelor's degree in engineering (i.e. B.E., B.Tech., or equivalent) in any one of the following (or equivalent) branches. Final-year students expecting to graduate by July 2026 may also apply. Admissions to the M.Tech (CSE) programme is on the basis of performance in the GATE examination. GATE scores (valid as of June 1, 2026) in CS - Computer Science and Information Technology will be considered for admission to the M.Tech. (CSE) programme. There is no fixed c" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/courses/mtech-cse-admissions" .

iiitb:mtech_ece_admissions a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Tech. ECE Admissions" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "Applications for the Academic Year 2026–27 are now open. [March 19, 2026]: Applications for the Academic Year 2026–27 are open. Candidates can apply via the link https://admissions.iiitb.net/ Click on the following links for more information about the programmes: The minimum qualification for admission to the M.Tech (ECE) programme is 65% in four-year bachelor's degree in engineering (i.e. B.E., B.Tech., or equivalent) in any one of the following (or equivalent) branches. Final-year students expecting to graduate by July 2026 may also apply. Admissions to the M.Tech (ECE) programme is on the basis of performance in the GATE examination. GATE scores (valid as of June 1, 2026) in EC - Electronics and Communication Engineering or in EE (Electrical Engineering) will be considered for admission" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/courses/mtech-ece-admissions" .

iiitb:mtech_electronics_and_communication_engineering a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "M.Tech (Electronics and Communication Engineering)" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "The goal of post graduate programmes at IIITB is to develop professionals of high quality to cater to the needs of industry and academia. Such education will be based on a broad grasp of the fundamental principles of the sciences and scientific methods, a deep understanding of specific area of specialization, an ability to solve new problems, and a capacity to learn continually and interact with multidisciplinary groups. Above all, IIITB aims at developing in its students a capacity for free and objective enquiry, courage and integrity, and awareness and sensitivity to the needs and aspirations of society. The postgraduate programs are designed with the above goals in view. They include courses of study, seminars, project work, and internships, or research leading to a thesis. M.Tech in El" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/academics/masters-programmes/mtech-electronics-and-communication-engineering" .

iiitb:naganand_yadati a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Naganand  Yadati" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "naganand [dot] yadati [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Naganand Yadati holds a PhD in Computer Science from the Indian Institute of Science, awarded in 2021. He specialises in machine learning and deep learning with expertise in graph neural networks and hypergraphs. His PhD focused on novel extensions of graph neural networks to hypergraphs. Before joining IIIT-Bangalore, he was a postdoctoral researcher at the National University of Singapore, where he focused on simplified models for graph learni" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/naganand" .

iiitb:narayanan_p_p a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Narayanan P. P." ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "narayanan [dot] pp [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Narayanan P. P. completed his Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology Palakkad in 2025, specialized in sensors, measurements, and instrumentation. His doctoral research focused on the development of novel capacitive and inductive sensor systems for accurate estimation of liquid level, dual-axis inclination, and two-component fluid composition, with applications in automotive, aerospace, and industrial sectors. He hol" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/narayanan-p-p" .

